1:
Rejoice in Yahweh, you righteous;
\q praise is appropriate for the upright.
\q

2:
Give thanks to Yahweh with the harp;
\q sing praises to him with the harp of ten strings.
\q

7:
He gathers the waters of the sea together like a heap;
\q he puts the oceans in storehouses.
\q

8:
Let the whole earth fear Yahweh;
\q let all the inhabitants of the world stand in awe of him.
\q

10:
Yahweh frustrates the alliances of nations;
\q he overrules the plans of the peoples.
\q

13:
Yahweh looks from heaven;
\q he sees all the people.
\q

16:
No king is saved by a vast army;
\q a warrior is not saved by his great strength.
\q

20:
We wait for Yahweh;
\q he is our help and our shield.
\q
